      "writtenOn": "2010-08-22T04:05:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Please do _not_ naively use strncat and strncpy since these functions will not properly zero-terminate the target buffer in case of overflow, leading to the risk of using/sending non-terminated strings in the program (which leads to security and hard to find bugs).\n\nquick fix is to use \u0027size-1\u0027 when calling these functions, and then always do a param_str[size-1] \u003d 0 before exiting.",
      "revId": "0fb79146a0604c595ef216dec0fd744dcc5f67c6",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
