      "side": 1,
      "message": "this is a bit too complex, and it leaks the strdup-ed strings anyway. You can modify the android_op_dns_server inplace instead to replace the commas by a 0, this will make for easier code. Example:\n\nwhile (*x) {\n  y \u003d strchr(x, \u0027,\u0027);\n  if (y !\u003d NULL) {\n    *y++ \u003d 0;\n  } else {\n    y \u003d x + strlen(x);\n  }\n  if (y \u003e x \u0026\u0026 add_dns_server(x) \u003d\u003d 0)\n    dns_count +\u003d 1;\n  x \u003d y;\n}",
      "revId": "0fb79146a0604c595ef216dec0fd744dcc5f67c6",
